Analyze Your Data

Salesforce Analytics Tools include Reports and Dashboards, Data Cloud Reports and Dashboards, CRM Analytics, Get Started Using CRM Analytics, Go Mobile with CRM Analytics.

Set Up the CRM Analytics Platform. Integrate Data into CRM Analytics Datasets. Gain Insights on Data Directly at Source.

Explore and Visualize Your Data in CRM Analytics. Learn to Explore Data. View Your Data in a Lens. Group Your Data into Categories. Filter Your Data.

Change the Sort Order. Change the Chart Type. Change Measures. Format Numbers. Drill Deeper Into Data.

Focus on Selected Data. Explore Multiple Datasets with a Single Query. Change the Chart Scale. Return to Previous Views. Limit the Size of Your Query Results.

View the Query Behind Your Lens. Clip a Lens to a Dashboard. Create a Model from a Lens. 

CRM Analytics uses Salesforce Analytics Query Language (SAQL) or Salesforce Object Query Language (SOQL) behind the scenes in lenses and dashboards.

Develop with CRM Analytics. Intelligent Analytics Apps. Tableau. Unified Analytics Experiences. Einstein Discovery.
title: Exploring Data in CRM Analytics
